note.p:
Pub. L. 98–497, title I, § 108, Oct. 19, 1984, 98 Stat. 2292, provided that: “For purposes of sections 103 through 106 [set out as notes above]— “(1) the term ‘Archivist’ means the Archivist of the United States appointed under section 2103 of title 44, United States Code, as added by section 102(a)(2) of this Act;
“(2) the term ‘Administration’ means the National Archives and Records Administration established under section 2102 of such title (as amended by section 101 of this Act); and
“(3) the term ‘function’ includes any duty, obligation, power, authority, responsibility, right, privilege, activity, or program.”
